    <since version=".NET 2.0" />
    <remarks>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>This exception indicates that an operation has been aborted by the consumer of an API. For example, if the event handler of the <see cref="E:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlBulkCopy.SqlRowsCopied" /> event sets the Abort property to true in the <see cref="T:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlRowsCopiedEventArgs" /> object passed to the handler, the <see cref="M:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlBulkCopy.WriteToServer" /> method stops sending rows to the server and throws an <see cref="T:System.Data.OperationAbortedException" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <summary>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>This exception is thrown when an ongoing operation is aborted by the user. </para>
    </summary>
  </Docs>
